erging modern cities in Europe, and even in America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCrimezTurkeyzIstanbulxHistory. 0aPunishmentzTurkeyzIstanbulxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  a18th century.  acivic.  acrime historians.  acrime history.  acrime.  acriminals.  acriminology.  aearly modern history.  aeconomic history.  agovernment and governing.  ahistorians.  ahistorical analysis.  aistanbul.  amediterranean.  amiddle east scholars.  amiddle east.  amulticultural society.  amurder.  anonfiction.  apolitical history.  aprostitution.  aretrospective.  arevisionist history.  ariots.  asocial change.  asocial sciences.  atheft.  atransgressions.  aturkey.  aturkish society.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094756640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947566423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947566/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles